I knew I was too far right just didn't correct enough to get this cliff).","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"07587e94-d77e-4817-8c07-b4d4f1b722f5","position":{"x":413.5647880614446,"y":552.935388867779},"comment":"Didn't see this reentrant to my left either and by here alarm bells were going off","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"a2b15331-cbc7-49aa-b794-399698789fb7","position":{"x":410.80713564382756,"y":656.9165756123523},"comment":"This was the original plan to 1","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"bf719a6b-f775-42e2-909f-e38deea89003","position":{"x":455.1441207508408,"y":373.20772685693436},"comment":"A little bit unsure where I was on the slope when I came up onto it, felt I was higher than I really was. To correct I think I should have planned to come from a bit higher up in that flat area then come to the rock from the top so it's an easier approach","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"e13a2365-9ab7-41c2-a0d8-fcdf609d73b7","position":{"x":728.8428844176275,"y":347.12562659369536},"comment":"A little stressed here with getting out of the green = bad exit direction. Should be a little more careful with checking the compass in the green and maybe a little more aggressive with the direction even if it's a bit rougher runnability","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"5e6e42f4-9a9c-4f54-9f25-dd7aa6b42158","position":{"x":873.5535322858591,"y":265.91619117333335},"comment":"A bit overrelying on the marshes here being readable rather than just focusing on the compass and pushing my way through the marsh, keeping my eyes up for the knolls and rocky hilltop which I think is the better approach here. Stop searching for the control!","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"a774b827-cd55-437c-83f7-8026c9ef34f9","position":{"x":670.5479473126794,"y":97.0945376624921},"comment":"Plan was to come more like this but the big giant rock in the edge of the field I thought was maybe alread at the hilltop since I was moving so slow. Very hesitant into the green area, got a bit luck with catching the big rocks and being smart with the direction and reading of the slope so I don't lose too much time.","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"2f95be5c-7dc4-4ce0-8b88-3ba50d66a90c","position":{"x":721.4043078684233,"y":835.7098481262026},"comment":"Red line here is what I thought I was doing by turning left there. Clearly did not have a good grasp on the direction, but also just again searching for the control when getting to the circle which is not entirely necessary here. I guess I thought I was further right than I was and didn't see the rocky part of the hilltop i was coming around.","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"},{"id":"fe755496-06ba-4c59-ab14-a72b66303ee4","position":{"x":376.88655887555905,"y":1172.721480182602},"comment":"Not the best exit direction here lost a few seconds, corrected well since I was checkign the compass and noticed I was a bit left but I think I could have saved some seconds just being ab it more aggressive out of the control even if it felt more runnable to the left","size":8,"color":"#e11d48"}]}